data.text:
Empowering Nonprofits with Dormie Network

Partnership That Transforms: Join Our Mission to Make a Positive Impact

Our Mission and Vision

Our mission is to foster enduring partnerships with nonprofit organizations, leveraging the allure and prestige of golf to enable impactful fundraising. Committed to social responsibility, we aim to transform the landscape of charitable giving through the unique opportunities our golf network provides. Our strategic collaborations empower nonprofit partners to exceed their fundraising goals, thereby magnifying their positive impact on society

Youth Golf Programs

Environmental Initiatives

Military and First Responders

Healthcare and Humanitarian

Working With the Dormie Network Foundation

Partnering with Dormie Network means joining a family that’s deeply committed to sparking positive change. Through our in-kind donations, cash grants and exclusive golf experiences, we provide your nonprofit with unique opportunities to raise critical funds. Our dedicated team ensures a smooth and fruitful collaboration, focusing on maximizing your fundraising potential.

Exclusive Access to Premier Golf Clubs

High-Value In-Kind Donations

Direct Financial Support Through Cash Grants

Exposure and Networking Opportunities

Our Nonprofit Impact

Since our inception, the Dormie Network Foundation has proudly contributed over $10.7 million to various causes, underscoring our commitment to making a tangible difference. Our partnerships span across four crucial pillars: youth golf, environmental initiatives, military/first responders and healthcare/humanitarian efforts, ensuring a wide-reaching and diverse impact.

Dormie Network Foundation Programs

The Dormie Network Foundation is dedicated to supporting non-profits through two key initiatives: our In-Kind Donation Program and our Cash Grant Program.

In-Kind

Our in-kind donations include national golf memberships that boost your fundraising events and directly contribute to your mission's success.

Cash Grants

Our cash grants provide direct financial support to further empower your projects and initiatives, ensuring your organization continues to thrive and make a difference.

Stories From the Heart

Partner Testimonials

“Working with Dormie Network’s Fundraising in a Box could not be any easier. They provide us with everything we need, from the winner’s certificate to marketing materials including professionally done videos and flyers, and more. Their team is always ready and willing to help in any way they can.”

Clark Harvey

Executive Director

Brighter Days Foundation

“Our relationship with the Dormie Network is great because it’s always a win/win/win situation. It’s a no-brainer for any nonprofit, with zero risk.

The Dormie Network in-kind donations generate far more than the minimum bid. We are grateful for their partnership-- DormieNetwork is a huge reason why we were able to provide Christmases for 200 families in need.”

Don Liimatainen

Founder & President/CEO

Best Christmas Ever

“Dormie Network’s generosity has made a true impact. The auction items have increased overall audience appeal and total revenue of our event auctions, which is great, because funds raised directly impact the lives of individuals and families impacted by autism worldwide,”

Jennifer Nicholas

Senior Events Coordinator for Els for Autism, headquartered in Jupiter, Florida.

“The unbelievable financial impact we have realized as a result of the generous contributions the Dormie Network Foundation made is beyond belief and has set a very high bar. To be associated with the Dormie Network significantly enhances our credibility to our donors, and their mindset and commitment to support is very welcome.”

Jeff Porter

Executive Director of First Tee – Omaha

“Donations like the in-kind from Dormie Network allow us to feed even more kids in the communities we support. Many of these communities don’t have the capacity to fundraise on their own, so high-value packages like these Stay and Plays as well as the donated memberships to Dormie Network help spread awareness of our cause and ensure we can keep growing the program.”

Beth Bush

Director of athletic and strategic partnerships

Embrace the opportunity to elevate your nonprofit with Dormie Network – where partnerships pave the way for impactful change.
